intro: Sicyos laciniatus, commonly known as the split-leaf sicyos, is a climbing plant native to Central and South America. It belongs to the family Cucurbitaceae, which includes cucumbers and gourds. The plant is characterized by its large, lobed leaves that can reach up to 1 meter in length. Its flowers are unisexual, with separate male and female flowers on the same plant. The fruit is a spherical, spiny capsule that contains several seeds.
